   - Properly interpreted "first insurance per item" rule by re-reading integration example carefully
   - Reasoned that 7 runes → 175 G means block requires *exactly* 3 (count === 3), not floor(count/3)
   - Confirmed cursed surcharge applies to item's base premium, first insurance applies to policy base premium (sum of item base premiums)
   - Recognized that block discount on components needs grouping by type (countByType)
